1)sudo (Super User DO) command in Linux is generally used as a prefix of some command that only superuser are allowed to run. 
If you prefix “sudo” with any command, it will run that command with elevated privileges or in other words allow a user with proper permissions to execute
a command as another user, such as the superuser

2) works with ubuntu's APT library to perform intstallion of new software packages, removing existing software packages, upgrading new software packakges and
even used to upgrade the entire operating system. 
